  stableDiffusion_positive_prompt_tooltip_updated: "Describe what you want to see. Use keywords for subject, art style, artists (e.g., 'by Greg Rutkowski'), mediums ('oil painting', '3D render'), lighting, colors, and composition. Use parentheses and colons for weighting, e.g., (keyword:1.3) for more emphasis.",
  stableDiffusion_comp_negative_prompt_label: "Negative Prompt (What to Avoid):",
  stableDiffusion_comp_negative_prompt_example_updated: "ugly, blurry, deformed, bad anatomy, extra limbs, watermark, text, signature, low quality, noise",
  stableDiffusion_negative_prompt_tooltip_updated: "Specify what you DON'T want to see. This is very important for cleaning up results and avoiding common artifacts.",
  stableDiffusion_comp_technical_params_label: "Technical Parameters (Optional):",
  stableDiffusion_comp_technical_params_example_updated: "Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, Steps: 25, CFG Scale: 7, Seed: 123456789, Size: 768x512",
  stableDiffusion_technical_params_tooltip_updated: "Depending on the interface: Sampler (e.g., Euler a, DPM++), Steps (e.g., 20-50), CFG Scale (how strongly the prompt guides the image, e.g., 5-15), Seed, Image Size. These are usually set in the UI, but can be part of a saved prompt concept.",

